cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper is about deep feature learning for person re-identification, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a structured graph Laplacian embedding algorithm, which involves optimization and learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper deals with image and video processing, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper also discusses the performance of the proposed method on different datasets, which involves evaluation and analysis, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible sub-category.
